The paper focuses on the use of convolutional neural networks for image segmentation, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors also explore different network architectures and machine learning techniques, indicating a focus on optimization and performance (cs.NE, cs.LG). Additionally, the application of the method is in the context of Alzheimer's disease mouse models, suggesting a potential intersection with artificial intelligence and bioinformatics (cs.AI, cs.BIO).
